,"text":"","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"31ad75f0-e87b-47e2-be97-9f1d4f4a5df5","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Lionardo,\u00A0\u2014\u00A0I have not replied earlier to thy last letter because I could not. As to thou taking a wife,\u00A0thou sayest it seems advisable to wait until the summer is over: if it appear so to thee it appears so to me. As to thy going to Loreto, as to thy going to Loreto on thy father\u0027s behalf, thou must go at all hazards if it be in fulfilment of a vow; if it be only for the repose of his soul I would much rather that thou shouldest give away the money that would be consumed by thy journey in alms for the love of God than do aught else with it; for if thou takest money to the priests, God knows what they may do with\u00A0it. Moreover it does not seem to be wise that thou shouldest waste the time just when thou art about to open a shop. And if thou wishest to prosper in thy business thou must be prepared to labour unceasingly\u00A0and to put on one side all the pleasant thoughts of youth. I have nothing else to add. As to the Corsi house, I should be glad to know if anything more\u00A0has ever been said to thee about it. Commend me to the priest, to Guicciardino and to Francesca.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"a69fca8f-57b7-45f9-9df0-e37d7ed150b6","type":"style/uppercase","start":0,"end":7,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"abf21dc6-1782-4360-9c8d-7dff590350d4","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":7,"value":"93ce2119-f2b8-4642-b551-7b8ca6b1ed96","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"7eab4395-c72d-4bb2-9209-28129181c47c","type":"attitude/explanation","start":12,"end":77,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"cb9fd0a1-ead0-4e45-a6ab-f295bf873713","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":12,"end":12,"value":"add92e01-cefe-4f13-94dd-f00eb82155b0","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"3f25693d-3da8-4c89-80b7-fab20ff4ebfb","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":42,"en